libcxgb4
------------------------------------------
libcxgb4 is a userspace driver for the Chelsio T4/T5 iWARP RNICs. It works as
a plug-in module for libibverbs that allows programs to use Chelsio RNICs
directly from userspace.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.9.0-3
  libibverbs1-1.2.1-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.28-3
  cygport-0.24.1-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-5
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://www.openfabrics.org/

Canonical download:
  https://www.openfabrics.org/downloads/cxgb4/libcxgb4-1.4.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libcxgb4-1.4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libcxgb4-1.4.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libcxgb4-1.4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcxgb4-1.4.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libcxgb4)
  /etc/libibverbs.d/cxgb4.driver
  /usr/bin/cygcxgb4-rdmav2.dll
  /usr/lib/libcxgb4.dll.a
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libcxgb4.README
  /usr/share/doc/libcxgb4/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libcxgb4/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libcxgb4/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libcxgb4/README

